defaultin 
defaultWales. 
default&#xa0;
default7.9.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCoeliac UK has produced a toolkit
default for Commissioners advising on 
defaultthe provision of gluten-free foods, which aims to support commissioners in developing a cost-effective, enhanced service through pharmacy-led prescriptions for patients with coeliac disease.
default&#xa0;
default7.10.
default&#xa0; 
defaultThrough the use of a pharmacy-led supply scheme
defaults
default, gluten-free foods are supplied directly from community pharmacists, thus
default minimising the workload for 
defaultGP practice
defaults
default. A review of established schemes in Northamptonshire and Cumbria show
defaults
default savings of between 20% and 40%. If this approach was applied nationally, there is the potential to save between £5 and £11 million per year in England alone, as well as freeing up GP time.
